<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="305" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="305">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="305">
Literature records large morphological variations for this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, PPC" journalOrPublisher="Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 167" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" refId="B30" refString="Hoek, PPC, 1881. Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873-76. Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger 3 (10): 1 - 167, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" title="Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873 - 76." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" volume="3" year="1881">Hoek 1881</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, TV" journalOrPublisher="Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 72" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/46595page/5/mode/1up" refId="B27" refString="Hodgson, TV, 1907. Pycnogonida. National Antarctic Expedition 1901-1904. Report of National Antarctic Expedition 1901-1904. Natural History 3: 1 - 72, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/46595page/5/mode/1up" title="Pycnogonida. National Antarctic Expedition 1901 - 1904. Report of National Antarctic Expedition 1901 - 1904." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/46595page/5/mode/1up" volume="3" year="1907">Hodgson 1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Loman, JCC" journalOrPublisher="Ministerio do Meio Ambiente, Brasilia" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" refId="B33" refString="Loman, JCC, 1923. The Pycnogonida of the Swedish Antarctic Expedition (1901-1903) (&quot;Antarctic&quot;). Further Zoological Results of the Swedish Antarctic Expedition 1901-1903 1(2): 1-41." title="The Pycnogonida of the Swedish Antarctic Expedition (1901 - 1903) (&quot; Antarctic &quot;). Further Zoological Results of the Swedish Antarctic Expedition 1901 - 1903 1 (2): 1 - 41." year="1923">Loman 1923</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, I" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Antarctic Research Expedition (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 72" refId="B22" refString="Gordon, I, 1944. Pycnogonida. Report of British Australian (and). New Zealand Antarctic Research Expedition (B) 5 (1): 1 - 72" title="Pycnogonida. Report of British Australian (and)." volume="5" year="1944">Gordon 1944</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" author="Child, CA" journalOrPublisher="Antarctic Research Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="113 - 160" refId="B10" refString="Child, CA, 1995b. Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV. Antarctic Research Series 69: 113 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" title="Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV." url="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" volume="69" year="1995 b">Child 1995b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" author="Weis, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="110 - 131" refId="B54" refString="Weis, A, Meyer, R, Dietz, L, Doemel, J, Leese, F, Melzer, RR, 2014. Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881)- A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 170 (1): 110 - 131, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" title="Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881) - A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" volume="170" year="2014">Weis et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). These variations encompass mainly the proportion of the articles of the legs, the shape of the trunk, the structure of the propodus, the size and inclination of the abdomen and the size of the cement gland (
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, JH" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="81 - 106" refId="B49" refString="Stock, JH, 1957. Pantopoden aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 2. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg 55: 81 - 106" title="Pantopoden aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 2." volume="55" year="1957">Stock 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pushkin, AF" journalOrPublisher="Exploration of the Fauna of the Seas" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 397" refId="B47" refString="Pushkin, AF, 1993. The pycnogonids fauna of the South Ocean: Biological results of the Soviet Antarctic expeditions. Exploration of the Fauna of the Seas 20: 1 - 397" title="The pycnogonids fauna of the South Ocean: Biological results of the Soviet Antarctic expeditions." volume="20" year="1993">Pushkin 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" author="Child, CA" journalOrPublisher="Antarctic Research Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="113 - 160" refId="B10" refString="Child, CA, 1995b. Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV. Antarctic Research Series 69: 113 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" title="Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV." url="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" volume="69" year="1995 b">Child 1995b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4585.3.7" author="Cano-Sanchez, E" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="517 - 530" refId="B7" refString="Cano-Sanchez, E, Lopez-Gonzalez, P, 2019. Two new species and new findings in the genus Pallenopsis (Pycnogonida: Pallenopsidae) with an updated identification key to Antarctic and sub-Antarctic species. Zootaxa 4585 (3): 517 - 530, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4585.3.7" title="Two new species and new findings in the genus Pallenopsis (Pycnogonida: Pallenopsidae) with an updated identification key to Antarctic and sub-Antarctic species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4585.3.7" volume="4585" year="2019">
Cano-Sanchez and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López-González">Lopez-Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4550.2.2" author="Scarabino, F" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="185 - 200" refId="B48" refString="Scarabino, F, Lucena, RA, Munilla, T, Soler-Membrives, A, Ortega, L, Schwindt, E, Lopez, G, Orensanz, JM, Christoffersen, ML, 2019. Pycnogonida (Arthropoda) from Uruguayan waters (Southwest Atlantic): Annotated checklist and biogeographic considerations. Zootaxa 4550 (2): 185 - 200, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4550.2.2" title="Pycnogonida (Arthropoda) from Uruguayan waters (Southwest Atlantic): Annotated checklist and biogeographic considerations." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4550.2.2" volume="4550" year="2019">Scarabino et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="305">
Recent studies, based mainly on molecular data, have indicated the existence of cryptic species under the name 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. patagonica" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly from the Antarctic Region (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" author="Weis, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="110 - 131" refId="B54" refString="Weis, A, Meyer, R, Dietz, L, Doemel, J, Leese, F, Melzer, RR, 2014. Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881)- A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 170 (1): 110 - 131, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" title="Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881) - A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" volume="170" year="2014">Weis et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" author="Harder, AM" journalOrPublisher="Polar Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="677 - 688" refId="B23" refString="Harder, AM, Halanych, KM, Mahon, AR, 2015. Diversity and distribution within the sea spider genus Pallenopsis (Chelicerata: Pycnogonida) in the Western Antarctic as revealed by mitochondrial DNA. Polar Biology 39 (4): 677 - 688, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" title="Diversity and distribution within the sea spider genus Pallenopsis (Chelicerata: Pycnogonida) in the Western Antarctic as revealed by mitochondrial DNA." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" volume="39" year="2015">Harder et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" author="Doemel, JS" journalOrPublisher="Frontiers in Ecology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 19" refId="B15" refString="Doemel, JS, Melzer, RR, Harder, AM, Mahon, AR, Leese, F, 2017. Nuclear and mitochondrial gene data support recent radiation within the sea spider species complex Pallenopsis patagonica. Frontiers in Ecology and Evolution 4 (139): 1 - 19, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" title="Nuclear and mitochondrial gene data support recent radiation within the sea spider species complex Pallenopsis patagonica." url="https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" volume="4" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dömel">Doemel</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" author="Doemel, JS" journalOrPublisher="Frontiers in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 29" refId="B16" refString="Doemel, JS, Macher, TH, Dietz, L, Duncan, S, Mayer, C, Rozenberg, A, Wolcott, K, Leese, L, Melzer, RR, 2019. Combining morphological and genomic data to resolve species diversity and study speciation processes of the Pallenopsis patagonica (Pycnogonida) species complex. Frontiers in Zoology 16 (36): 1 - 29, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" title="Combining morphological and genomic data to resolve species diversity and study speciation processes of the Pallenopsis patagonica (Pycnogonida) species complex." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" volume="16" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
). These species form the 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. patagonica" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">sensu lato</emphasis>
complex. Although no consensus exists concerning the number of possible new species (up to 19 clades have been proposed) and no morphological characterisation has been provided for the identified clades, specimens collected in the Falkland Islands and the Patagonian Region appear to belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. patagonica" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">sensu stricto</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" author="Weis, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="110 - 131" refId="B54" refString="Weis, A, Meyer, R, Dietz, L, Doemel, J, Leese, F, Melzer, RR, 2014. Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881)- A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 170 (1): 110 - 131, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" title="Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881) - A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" volume="170" year="2014">Weis et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" author="Harder, AM" journalOrPublisher="Polar Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="677 - 688" refId="B23" refString="Harder, AM, Halanych, KM, Mahon, AR, 2015. Diversity and distribution within the sea spider genus Pallenopsis (Chelicerata: Pycnogonida) in the Western Antarctic as revealed by mitochondrial DNA. Polar Biology 39 (4): 677 - 688, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" title="Diversity and distribution within the sea spider genus Pallenopsis (Chelicerata: Pycnogonida) in the Western Antarctic as revealed by mitochondrial DNA." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-015-1823-8" volume="39" year="2015">Harder et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" author="Doemel, JS" journalOrPublisher="Frontiers in Ecology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 19" refId="B15" refString="Doemel, JS, Melzer, RR, Harder, AM, Mahon, AR, Leese, F, 2017. Nuclear and mitochondrial gene data support recent radiation within the sea spider species complex Pallenopsis patagonica. Frontiers in Ecology and Evolution 4 (139): 1 - 19, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" title="Nuclear and mitochondrial gene data support recent radiation within the sea spider species complex Pallenopsis patagonica." url="https://doi.org/10.3389/fevo.2016.00139" volume="4" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dömel">Doemel</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" author="Doemel, JS" journalOrPublisher="Frontiers in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 29" refId="B16" refString="Doemel, JS, Macher, TH, Dietz, L, Duncan, S, Mayer, C, Rozenberg, A, Wolcott, K, Leese, L, Melzer, RR, 2019. Combining morphological and genomic data to resolve species diversity and study speciation processes of the Pallenopsis patagonica (Pycnogonida) species complex. Frontiers in Zoology 16 (36): 1 - 29, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" title="Combining morphological and genomic data to resolve species diversity and study speciation processes of the Pallenopsis patagonica (Pycnogonida) species complex." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12983-019-0316-y" volume="16" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
), the type locality of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="305">
The specimen analysed herein comes from northern Argentina, close to the northern range of the species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" author="Child, CA" journalOrPublisher="Antarctic Research Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="113 - 160" refId="B10" refString="Child, CA, 1995b. Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV. Antarctic Research Series 69: 113 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" title="Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida V. The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae, and Callipallenidae, including the genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic seas XXIV." url="https://doi.org/10.1029/AR069p0113" volume="69" year="1995 b">Child 1995b</bibRefCitation>
). This female individual has all the characters described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, PPC" journalOrPublisher="Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 167" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" refId="B30" refString="Hoek, PPC, 1881. Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873-76. Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger 3 (10): 1 - 167, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" title="Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873 - 76." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" volume="3" year="1881">Hoek (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, such as the indicated number of articles and the proportion established amongst the last articles of the ovigers, the same proportion amongst the articles of the legs and a similar body structure, with lateral processes separated by about less than half their own diameter and a cylindrical proboscis. In relation to subsequent descriptions, the present specimen is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. meridionalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(today a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. patagonica" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), particularly in the shape of the ocular tubercle, structure of the propodus and ornamentation of the lateral processes (
<bibRefCitation author="Pushkin, AF" journalOrPublisher="Exploration of the Fauna of the Seas" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 397" refId="B47" refString="Pushkin, AF, 1993. The pycnogonids fauna of the South Ocean: Biological results of the Soviet Antarctic expeditions. Exploration of the Fauna of the Seas 20: 1 - 397" title="The pycnogonids fauna of the South Ocean: Biological results of the Soviet Antarctic expeditions." volume="20" year="1993">Pushkin 1993</bibRefCitation>
). However, the closest proximity is with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. yepayekae" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="yepayekae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. yepayekae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" author="Weis, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="110 - 131" refId="B54" refString="Weis, A, Meyer, R, Dietz, L, Doemel, J, Leese, F, Melzer, RR, 2014. Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881)- A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 170 (1): 110 - 131, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" title="Pallenopsis patagonica (Hoek, 1881) - A species complex revealed by morphology and DNA barcoding with description of a new species of Pallenopsis Wilson, 1881." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12097" volume="170" year="2014">Weis et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
, from which it may be distinguished by the number of articles on the oviger and in the number of setae on the abdomen (2 in the description, 4 in the individual at hand), including a cylindrical proboscis. However, we observed an undescribed character for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. patagoica" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="patagoica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. patagoica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but reported for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. yepayekae" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="yepayekae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. yepayekae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and indicated as distinguishing the two species: the presence of brush-like setae in the ventral region of coxae 2 and 3. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, PPC" journalOrPublisher="Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 167" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" refId="B30" refString="Hoek, PPC, 1881. Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873-76. Reports of the Scientific Results of the Exploring Voyage of HMS Challenger 3 (10): 1 - 167, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" title="Report on the Pycnogonida dredged by HMS Challenger 1873 - 76." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13070408" volume="3" year="1881">Hoek (1881)</bibRefCitation>
described the presence of setae in coxae 2 and 3, but did not illustrate them. In the cited material, such setae appear to be smaller and in lower number in the material analysed herein than in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. yepayekae" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" rank="species" species="yepayekae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="305">P. yepayekae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="305">
Great morphological variation has been reported for several species from polar, temperate and tropical regions, where the genus is quite diverse (
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, JH" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" pagination="957 - 1092" refId="B51" refString="Stock, JH, 1974. Pycnogonids from the continental shelf, slope and deep sea of the tropical Atlantic and East Pacific. Bulletin of Marine Science 24: 957 - 1092" title="Pycnogonids from the continental shelf, slope and deep sea of the tropical Atlantic and East Pacific." volume="24" year="1974">Stock 1974</bibRefCitation>
). Our data are insufficient for advancing previous taxonomic conclusions. It becomes necessary to conduct more in-depth morphological analysis and to extend the investigation to include samples from wider geographical locations. Species-group and genus-level revisions are necessary to distinguish diagnostic species characters from intrapopulational variations (
<bibRefCitation author="Hennig, W" journalOrPublisher="Deutscher Zentralverlag, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" refId="B24" refString="Hennig, W, 1950. Grundzuege einer Theorie der phylogenetischen Systematik. Deutscher Zentralverlag, Berlin" title="Grundzuege einer Theorie der phylogenetischen Systematik." year="1950">Hennig 1950</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hennig, W" journalOrPublisher="Editora Universitaria de Buenos Aires, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="305" refId="B25" refString="Hennig, W, 1968. Elementos de una sistematica filogenetica. Editora Universitaria de Buenos Aires, Buenos Aires" title="Elementos de una sistematica filogenetica." year="1968">1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
